The paper focuses on developing an online method for mobile robots to incrementally build a semantically rich 3-D point cloud of the environment. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the proposed method is specifically designed for mobile robots. The method involves using a deep neural network for semantic segmentation, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of accurate semantic processing for context-aware decision making, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the proposed method involves using a multi-view context pooling operator to improve classification accuracy, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
